  "extendedContent": [
    {
      "title": "The 99 Beautiful Names",
      "content": "The Asma al-Husna represent the divine attributes revealed in the Quran and Hadith. Key names include: Ar-Rahman (The Most Compassionate), Ar-Rahim (The Most Merciful), Al-Malik (The Sovereign), Al-Quddus (The Holy), As-Salam (The Source of Peace), Al-Khaliq (The Creator), Al-Ghaffar (The Forgiver), Al-Wahid (The One), and As-Samad (The Eternal). Each name reflects an aspect of divine nature accessible to human understanding."
    },
    {
      "title": "Tawhid - Divine Oneness",
      "content": "The fundamental doctrine of Islam, Tawhid declares the absolute oneness of Allah. It comprises three aspects: Tawhid ar-Rububiyyah (Oneness of Lordship - Allah alone is Creator and Sustainer), Tawhid al-Uluhiyyah (Oneness of Worship - worship directed to Allah alone), and Tawhid al-Asma wa's-Sifat (Oneness of Names and Attributes - Allah's unique divine attributes)."
    }
  ],
